metadata.name: Solitude
metadata.description:
UNSEEN is a collection dedicated to the pine and oak woodlands of Madrid.

This small mountain range has served as the recreational area for Spanish Royalty.
It has also witnessed many historical events, such as a triumphal battle by Napoleon, and in the same steep hills, the horrid combat depicted in Hemingway ´s novel “For Whom The Bell Tolls” during the Spanish Civil war.

A small glimpse at any given site, and a bit of imagination, can take you back centuries in time.
